[{"id":"553cfbcf99acdef0c79dc76abeb6757a","from":"J. Epstein","from_email":"jeeproject@yahoo.com","to":"jpm6929@aol.com","to_list":[{"name":"jpm6929@aol.com","email":"jpm6929@aol.com"}],"cc_list":[],"subject":"Re: Late answer","date":"2007-03-15T02:11:39.000Z","formatted_date":"Mar 15, 2007","formatted_time":"2:11 AM","body":"nothing came through please email again\n\n\n----- Original Message ----\nFrom: \"jpm6929@aol.com\" <jpm6929@aol.com>\nTo: jeeproject@yahoo.com\nCc: daschoettle@yahoo.com; lagonda@molyneuxstudio.com\nSent: Wednesday, March 14, 2007 7:05:42 PM\nSubject: Late answer\n\n\n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n \n \n \nJeffrey, It is true that more than a month ago Charles told Doug that the return was (silly?) in the baseboard, but I have not heard from anyone from McGuire to give us any indication on the mechanical. Are they expecting also from us to draw in the interior elevations the exact location of all the air grilles that so far no one has designed? Maybe they were in all those drawings that they threw away, that I never saw. Anyway, I thought that the purpose of sending them the drawings was to discuss them and make the corrections or changes, to just say who the hell is drawing them is not very nice.\nThe elevations are the same as before, (your Doug said to me many times that for the time beeing that was not at all important) while I , as I told you, am doing (against all bets ) a try using the local stone ( not the bluebitch ) for the facade of the Pool House and your office. The stone mason will be in the island the last week of March, and of the samples of what  he has seen that I took in a bag on my last trip ,he thinks is good. I will finish the drawing, if you want, even though we are not that sure yet that we can mill that stone. J.P. \n \n-----Original Message-----\nFrom: jeeproject@yahoo.com\nTo: jpm6929@aol.com\nSent: Wed, 14 Mar 2007 3:30 PM\nSubject: Re: Island, House in the island and Moscow\n \n \n.\n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n. \n\n\nAOL now offers free email to everyone. Find out more about what's free from AOL at AOL.com.\n\n\n \n____________________________________________________________________________________\n8:00? 8:25? 8:40? Find a flick in no time \nwith the Yahoo! Search movie showtime shortcut.\nhttp://tools.search.yahoo.com/shortcuts/#news","body_html":"<html><head><style type=\"text/css\"><!-- DIV {margin:0px;} --></style></head><body><div style=\"font-family:times new roman, new york, times, serif;font-size:12pt\"><DIV style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman, new york, times, serif\">nothing came through please email again<BR><BR>\n<DIV style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman, new york, times, serif\">----- Original Message ----<BR>From: \"jpm6929@aol.com\" &lt;jpm6929@aol.com&gt;<BR>To: jeeproject@yahoo.com<BR>Cc: daschoettle@yahoo.com; lagonda@molyneuxstudio.com<BR>Sent: Wednesday, March 14, 2007 7:05:42 PM<BR>Subject: Late answer<BR><BR>\n<DIV><SPAN style=\"DISPLAY: inline-block\"></SPAN>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\">\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" size=3></FONT></DIV><SPAN><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" size=3>&nbsp; </FONT></SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><SPAN><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" size=3>&nbsp; </FONT></SPAN></DIV>\n<DIV class=MsoNormal style=\"MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt\"><SPAN><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" size=3